  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guinea 2021 Ebola Outbreak</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On the 14th of February 2021, health authorities in Guinea declared an Ebola outbreak in the rural community of Gou&#xC3;&#xA9;k&#xC3;&#xA9; in N&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;Zerekore prefecture. Due to the location of the outbreak, there is a high risk of the outbreak spreading to neighbouring countries.&#xC2;&#xA0;
IFRC has launched a multi-country Emergency Appeal on the 19th Feb 2021 with a total budget of CHF 8.5 million. The overall objective of the Appeal is to reduce morbidity and mortality resulting from the EVD outbreak in Guinea, and to prepare for, prevent and rapidly contain outbreaks of EVD should the virus spread to other regions of Guinea and neighbouring countries (Sierra Leone, Liberia, C&#xC3;&#xB4;te d&#xC2;&#xB4;Ivoire, Mali and Senegal).&#xC2;&#xA0;
BRC&apos;s Ebola Appeal is open (using the same as for the DRC outbreak).&#xC2;</narrative>
  </description>
